# Owner workflow preferences

When the owner states a **recurring** process preference (git/PR, terminals, review gates, etc.):

1. Apply it in this session.
2. Persist in `.cursor/rules/`: update the existing topic file, or add a focused `.mdc`. Prefer **`globs` + `alwaysApply: false`** when the rule only matters for certain files; use `alwaysApply: true` only for gates that apply every turn.
3. Tell the owner which rule file changed (one line).

Do not wait for “add this to instructions” if it clearly applies every time.

**Index:** git/PR → `git-push-approval.mdc`; cost → `agent-cost-optimization.mdc`; PowerShell → `windows-powershell-shell.mdc`; terminals → `terminal-hygiene.mdc`; UI responsive → `desktop-mobile-design.mdc`; company data/research → `company-data.mdc`; publish → `21_PUBLISHING.md`.

Do **not** persist: one-off task details; product decisions (use `.playbook/12_DECISIONS.md` / `13_CHANGELOG.md`); secrets unless the owner asked to store them.
